starentMIB.contactinfo: Email: support@starentnetworks.com Web: www.cisco.com Cisco Systems, Inc. 30 International Place Tewksbury, MA 01876 (978) 851-1100
starentMIB.description: Cisco Systems ASR 5xxx series of multimedia core platforms (ASR 5000, ASR 5500) Designed exclusively for mobile and fixed mobile converged applications, Cisco's ASR 5xxx series products provide a high-performance, highly intelligent platform ideally suited for development in mobile operator networks to fulfill key multimedia core networking functions. The platform features 2G/3G/4G and WiFi multi-service access indepedent capabilities coupled with a carrier class high-availability design. Harnessing subscriber awareness with an abundant supply of distributed processing resources, the ASR 5xxx series offers a variety of high touch Inline Services to enable service providers to monetize the value of the network while enriching the overall subscriber experience.

StarentSlotType.name: StarentSlotType
StarentSlotType.description: Describes the type of a slot. Each slot in the chassis is build to contain specific type(s) of cards. Only a card of one of the appropriate types can be put into a specific slot.

StarentCardType.name: StarentCardType
StarentCardType.description: Describes the type of a card. Each type represents a physically different card which would have a unique part number.

StarRelayState.name: StarRelayState
StarRelayState.description: The state of a Central Office (CO) relay.

StarLongDurTimeoutAction.name: StarLongDurTimeoutAction
StarLongDurTimeoutAction.description: The action taken by the system upon detection of a long-duration session

StarShortName.name: StarShortName
StarShortName.description: A short identification string. Follows the same conventions as the DisplayString TEXTUAL-CONVENTION.

StarShortID.name: StarShortID
StarShortID.description: An abbreviated form for identifying a service, composed of the first 8 characters of the context name, and the first 8 characters of a service name, seperated by (:)

StarMediumID.name: StarMediumID
StarMediumID.description: An abbreviated form for identifying a context-specific object, composed of the first 8 characters of the context name, and the first 16 characters of the object name, seperated by (:)

StarENBID.name: StarENBID
StarENBID.description: An eNodeB identifier in the form aaa:bbb:cccccccc

starChassisCriticalCO.name: starChassisCriticalCO
starChassisCriticalCO.description: The current state of the Critical Central Office (CO) relay

starChassisMajorCO.name: starChassisMajorCO
starChassisMajorCO.description: The current state of the Major Central Office (CO) relay

starChassisMinorCO.name: starChassisMinorCO
starChassisMinorCO.description: The current state of the Minor Central Office (CO) relay

starChassisAction.name: starChassisAction
starChassisAction.description: Trigger to perform certain system-wide operations. noaction(1) performs no operation. It is the normal value received when this attribute is read. aco(2) triggers the Alarm Cut-Off, which shuts off all of the Central Office (CO) audible/visual relays. reset(3) triggers a system-wide restart. It will completely disrupt service on the device.

starChassisAudibleAlarm.name: starChassisAudibleAlarm
starChassisAudibleAlarm.description: The current state of the chassis Audible Alarm

starChassisUTCTime.name: starChassisUTCTime
starChassisUTCTime.description: The current time on the chassis, in UTC format

starChassisLocalTime.name: starChassisLocalTime
starChassisLocalTime.description: The current time on the chassis, converted to the local timezone

starChassisDescription.name: starChassisDescription
starChassisDescription.description: A brief description of the chassis

starChassisSWRevision.name: starChassisSWRevision
starChassisSWRevision.description: The software revision running on the chassis

starChassisPeakCpuUsage.name: starChassisPeakCpuUsage
starChassisPeakCpuUsage.description: Percentage of the system level peak cpu usage.starChassisPeakCpuUsage is the percentage value times 100; for example,2.3% would be represented as 230

starChassisPeakMemoryUsage.name: starChassisPeakMemoryUsage
starChassisPeakMemoryUsage.description: The system level peak memory usage, in kilobytes, rounded down (i.e. 1023 bytes = 0 kilobytes)

starSlotTable.name: starSlotTable
starSlotTable.description: A table containing information on all of the slots

starCardType.name: starCardType
starCardType.description: The type of the card which is plugged into a slot

starCardOperState.name: starCardOperState
starCardOperState.description: The current operational state of the card

starCardAdminState.name: starCardAdminState
starCardAdminState.description: The administrative state of the card

starCardRevision.name: starCardRevision
starCardRevision.description: The revision number of the card that is physically present in this slot

starCardLastStateChange.name: starCardLastStateChange
starCardLastStateChange.description: The time when the last state change occurred for this row. A manager could poll this variable to determine if information has changed.

starCardMode.name: starCardMode
starCardMode.description: The desired mode of the card. This field is applicable only to slots which can contain PAC/PSC and TAC cards. The active(4) value is obsolete and has been replaces with activepac(5) and activetac(6)

starCardLock.name: starCardLock
starCardLock.description: Identifies if the card lock is currently engaged. A value of locked(2) means that the lock is engaged, and thus the card could not be removed from the chassis. A value of unlocked(3) means that the lock is not engaged, and an operator could remove the card from the chassis. A value of unknown(1) should represent that there is no card physically in the slot.

starCardRebootPending.name: starCardRebootPending
starCardRebootPending.description: Identifies if a reboot operation is currently pending for this card.

starCardUsable.name: starCardUsable
starCardUsable.description: Identifies if the card is currently usable.

starCardSinglePOF.name: starCardSinglePOF
starCardSinglePOF.description: Identifies if this card represents a single point of failure (POF). A value of no(1) indicates that this card is supported by a redundant card which can take over in the event of a failure. A value of yes(2) indicates that this card does not have a redundant partner, and that a failure of this card could result in service interruption.

starCardAttachment.name: starCardAttachment
starCardAttachment.description: Identifies if the card is currently attached to another card (a PAC/PSC attached to a line card, or visa versa, for example

starCardTemperature.name: starCardTemperature
starCardTemperature.description: The temperature, in degrees Celcius, as measured on the card. A value of 0 indicates that the temperature cannot be read, or that the card is not present. The maximum measurable temperature is 70 C

starSlotVoltage1dot5.name: starSlotVoltage1dot5
starSlotVoltage1dot5.description: The current voltage, in millivolts, of the nominal 1.5V power supply. The working range for this card is the range defined by variables starSlotVoltage1dot5LowThresh and starSlotVoltage1dot5HighThresh. A value of 0 indicates that this voltage level is not present on this card, or that the card is not present. This attribute is obsolete.

starSlotVoltage1dot5LowThresh.name: starSlotVoltage1dot5LowThresh
starSlotVoltage1dot5LowThresh.description: The voltage level, in millivolts, which is the lowest allowable value for the nominal 1.5V power supply. A value of 0 indicates that there is no card present. This attribute is obsolete.

starSlotVoltage1dot5HighThresh.name: starSlotVoltage1dot5HighThresh
starSlotVoltage1dot5HighThresh.description: The voltage level, in millivolts, which is the highest allowable value for the nominal 1.5V power supply. A value of 0 indicates that there is no card present. This attribute is obsolete.

starSlotVoltage1dot8LowThresh.name: starSlotVoltage1dot8LowThresh
starSlotVoltage1dot8LowThresh.description: The voltage level, in millivolts, which is the lowest allowable value for the nominal 1.8V power supply. A value of 0 indicates that there is no card present. This attribute is obsolete.

starSlotVoltage1dot8HighThresh.name: starSlotVoltage1dot8HighThresh
starSlotVoltage1dot8HighThresh.description: The voltage level, in millivolts, which is the highest allowable value for the nominal 1.8V power supply. A value of 0 indicates that there is no card present. This attribute is obsolete.

starSlotVoltage2dot5LowThresh.name: starSlotVoltage2dot5LowThresh
starSlotVoltage2dot5LowThresh.description: The voltage level, in millivolts, which is the lowest allowable value for the nominal 2.5V power supply. A value of 0 indicates that there is no card present. This attribute is obsolete.

starSlotVoltage2dot5HighThresh.name: starSlotVoltage2dot5HighThresh
starSlotVoltage2dot5HighThresh.description: The voltage level, in millivolts, which is the highest allowable value for the nominal 2.5V power supply. A value of 0 indicates that there is no card present. This attribute is obsolete.

starSlotVoltage3dot3LowThresh.name: starSlotVoltage3dot3LowThresh
starSlotVoltage3dot3LowThresh.description: The voltage level, in millivolts, which is the lowest allowable value for the nominal 3.3V power supply. A value of 0 indicates that there is no card present. This attribute is obsolete.

starSlotVoltage3dot3HighThresh.name: starSlotVoltage3dot3HighThresh
starSlotVoltage3dot3HighThresh.description: The voltage level, in millivolts, which is the highest allowable value for the nominal 3.3V power supply. A value of 0 indicates that there is no card present. This attribute is obsolete.

The working range for this card is the range defined by variables starSlotVoltage5dot0LowThresh and starSlotVoltage5dot0HighThresh. A value of 0 indicates that the voltage cannot be read, or that the card is not present. This attribute is obsolete.

starSlotVoltage5dot0LowThresh.name: starSlotVoltage5dot0LowThresh
starSlotVoltage5dot0LowThresh.description: The voltage level, in millivolts, which is the lowest allowable value for the nominal 5.0V power supply. A value of 0 indicates that there is no card present. This attribute is obsolete.

starSlotVoltage5dot0HighThresh.name: starSlotVoltage5dot0HighThresh
starSlotVoltage5dot0HighThresh.description: The voltage level, in millivolts, which is the highest allowable value for the nominal 5.0V power supply. A value of 0 indicates that there is no card present. This attribute is obsolete.

starSlotNumPorts.name: starSlotNumPorts
starSlotNumPorts.description: Number of data ports on this card. This value will be 0 for cards that do not contain ports, such as SPC/SMC/PAC/PSC/TAC cards, or for slots which do not contain a card. This attribute is obsolete.

starSlotAction.name: starSlotAction
starSlotAction.description: Trigger to perform certain slot operations. noaction(1) performs no operation. It is the normal value received when this attribute is read. reset(2) causes the slot to be reset

starSlotVoltageState.name: starSlotVoltageState
starSlotVoltageState.description: The state of the voltage supplies on the card. A value of unknown(0) means that the state cannot be identified; normal(1) represents a properly functioning card; outofrange(2) indicates that one or more voltage sources are not within their specified operating range.

starSlotNumCPU.name: starSlotNumCPU
starSlotNumCPU.description: The number of general-purpose CPUs on this card

starSlotPartNumber.name: starSlotPartNumber
starSlotPartNumber.description: The part number of this card

starSlotPartRevision.name: starSlotPartRevision
starSlotPartRevision.description: The revision number of this card

starSlotSerialNumber.name: starSlotSerialNumber
starSlotSerialNumber.description: The serial number of this card

starSlotCLEICode.name: starSlotCLEICode
starSlotCLEICode.description: The CLEI code of this card

starSlotCiscoModelName.name: starSlotCiscoModelName
starSlotCiscoModelName.description: Cisco-defined Product Identifier (PID). The PID is an alphanumeric identifier used to identify specific Cisco product hardware, and may be up to 18 characters in length. starSlotCiscoModelName will be blank (zero characters) if no PID is available.

starSlotCiscoHardwareRev.name: starSlotCiscoHardwareRev
starSlotCiscoHardwareRev.description: Cisco-defined Version Identifier (VID). The VID is used to track the version of the Customer-Orderable Cisco Product Identifier (PID) [starSlotCiscoModelName]. The data convention for VID is 'V' followed by a two digit number. VID numbering typically begins at 'V01' but can be initiated at a higher value. starSlotCiscoHardwareRev will be blank (zero characters) if no VID is available.

starSlotCiscoSerialNumber.name: starSlotCiscoSerialNumber
starSlotCiscoSerialNumber.description: Cisco-defined Serial Number (SN). The SN is an 11 character identifier used in conjunction with the Cisco Product Identifier (PID) [starSlotCiscoModelName] to identify a unique product or Field Replaceable Unit (FRU) of a product. starSlotCiscoSerialNumber will be blank (zero characters) if no VID is available.

starSlotMappingTable.name: starSlotMappingTable
starSlotMappingTable.description: A table identifying all of the slot mappings. This table is applicable only to starChassisType ASR5000 platform.

starSlotMappingEntry.name: starSlotMappingEntry
starSlotMappingEntry.description: Information about a particular slot mapping

starSlotMappingNum.name: starSlotMappingNum
starSlotMappingNum.description: The slot number. This always represents a slot in the back of the chassis.

starSlotMappingType.name: starSlotMappingType
starSlotMappingType.description: The type of the slot mapping. The value none(1) represents that there is no mapping, which typically represents that there is no card present in this slot.

starSlotMappingRCCNum.name: starSlotMappingRCCNum
starSlotMappingRCCNum.description: Identifies which RCC card is responsible for this mapping. This value is only valid if the value of starSlotMappingType is rcc(3).

starSlotMappingToSlot.name: starSlotMappingToSlot
starSlotMappingToSlot.description: The slot number this slot is mapped to. This always represents a slot in the front of the chassis

starFanTable.name: starFanTable
starFanTable.description: A table containing information on all of the fan controllers

starFanEntry.name: starFanEntry
starFanEntry.description: Information about a particular fan controller

starFanLocation.name: starFanLocation
starFanLocation.description: The physical location of the fan controller

starFanStatus.name: starFanStatus
starFanStatus.description: A bitmask representing the status of the fan tray. 0x01 All Fans Good 0x02 Multiple Fans Bad 0x04 Single Fan Bad 0x08 HB Error 0x10 COM A Error 0x20 COM B Error 0x40 COMM Error 0x80 Not Present 0x100 Present 0x200 Filter Clogged 0x400 Unknown A normal, properly functioning fan tray would show 0x101 (257 decimal), meaning it is present (0x100) and all fans are working (0x1)

starFanSpeed.name: starFanSpeed
starFanSpeed.description: The speed of the fans controlled by this fan controller. The values represent the percentage that the speed is running relative to the maximum possible speed, speed100(12)

starLogTable.name: starLogTable
starLogTable.description: A table containing information about all of the system logs

starLogEntry.name: starLogEntry
starLogEntry.description: Information about a particular system log

starLogName.name: starLogName
starLogName.description: The name of the system log

starLogCurSize.name: starLogCurSize
starLogCurSize.description: The size, in bytes, of this log

starLogMaxSize.name: starLogMaxSize
starLogMaxSize.description: The maximum size, in bytes, of this log

starMaxAlertsPerTime.name: starMaxAlertsPerTime
starMaxAlertsPerTime.description: The maximum number of SNMP Traps which will be sent within the time period specified by starWindowTime

starWindowTime.name: starWindowTime
starWindowTime.description: The amount of time within which no more than starMaxAlertsPerTime SNMP Traps will be sent.

starAlertSendingEnabled.name: starAlertSendingEnabled
starAlertSendingEnabled.description: Shows if SNMP traps are currently enabled or disabled. Traps are disabled when more than starMaxAlertsPerTime traps are sent within the starWindowTime time period. A value of true(1) indicates that traps will still be sent. A value of false(2) indicates that traps are no longer being generated

starPowerTable.name: starPowerTable
starPowerTable.description: A table containing information about all power filters

starPowerEntry.name: starPowerEntry
starPowerEntry.description: Information about a particular power filter

starPowerNumber.name: starPowerNumber
starPowerNumber.description: The identifying number for this power filter.

starPowerState.name: starPowerState
starPowerState.description: The state of the power filter. The value active(1) means that the power filter is present and operational. The value failed(2) means that the power filter is present, but not operational. The value not-present(3) means that the power filter is not physically present in the system.

starCPUTable.name: starCPUTable
starCPUTable.description: A table containing information about all CPUs

starCPUSlot.name: starCPUSlot

starBfdSrcAddressType.name: starBfdSrcAddressType
starBfdSrcAddressType.description: This object specifies IP address type of the source IP address of this BFD session. Only values unknown(0), ipv4(1), ipv6(2), or ipv6z(4) have to be supported. The value of unknown(0) is allowed only when the session is singleHop(1) and the source IP address of this BFD session is derived from the outgoing interface, or when the BFD session is not associated with a specific interface.

starBfdSrcAddress.name: starBfdSrcAddress
starBfdSrcAddress.description: This object specifies the source IP address of this BFD session.

starBfdDstAddressType.name: starBfdDstAddressType
starBfdDstAddressType.description: This object specifies IP address type of the neighboring IP address which is being monitored with this BFD session. Only values unknown(0), ipv4(1), ipv6(2), or ipv6z(4) have to be supported. The value of unknown(0) is allowed only when the session is singleHop(1) and the outgoing interface is of type point-to-point, or when the BFD session is not associated with a specific interface.

starBfdDstAddress.name: starBfdDstAddress
starBfdDstAddress.description: This object specifies the neighboring IP address which is being monitored with this BFD session.

starBfdLocalDisc.name: starBfdLocalDisc
starBfdLocalDisc.description: This object specifies the local discriminator for this BFD session, used to uniquely identify it

starBfdRemDisc.name: starBfdRemDisc
starBfdRemDisc.description: This object specifies the session discriminator chosen by the remote system for this BFD session. The value may be zero(0) if the remote discriminator is not yet known or if the session is in the down or adminDown(1) state.

starBfdSessDiagCode.name: starBfdSessDiagCode
starBfdSessDiagCode.description: A diagnostic code specifying the local system's reason for the last transition of the session from up(4) to some other state.

starSRPSwitchReason.name: starSRPSwitchReason
starSRPSwitchReason.description: A Switchover code specifying the SRP's Switchover reason. The following reasons would appear when chassis transitioning from Active to Standby State: notDefined(0), aaaFailure(1), bgpFailure(2), bfdFailure(3), diameterFailure(4), hsrpSwitchover(5), dualActive(7) manualSwitchOver(11), egqcFailure(12), The following reasons would appear when chassis transitioning from Standby to Pending Active State: notDefined(0), chassisChassisBfdFailure(6), deadTimerExpiry(9)

A value of raid(2) means that this device is a raid array. A value of raidmember(3) means the device is part of a raid array, and thus cannot be read/written to outside of the raid array

starMMES1PathSvcID.name: starMMES1PathSvcID
